        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you repair my Thermador Freedom column without pulling it from the cabinetry?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, for most service. Compressor replacement, evaporator fan motor, defrost thermostat, condenser fan motor, control board, door gasket, and ice maker harness work all happen through the toe-kick and rear access points without removing the column from the millwork. We pull the column only for sealed refrigerant-system work or a seized compressor requiring brazed-line access. When that's necessary, we document the cabinetry before disassembly — photos of trim, labels on shims — and reseat to the factory 1/8\" flush spec."
