          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Five common causes in order of frequency: clogged water supply line or frozen fill tube (easy fix, 30 min), failed water inlet valve ($165–$240 part), failed ice maker module ($285–$420 — the whole assembly at the top of the cavity), failed thermostat (the ice maker needs to reach 15°F before it cycles — $125 part), or a failed control board talking to the ice maker harness. We diagnose by running a manual harvest cycle and testing the water feed, motor, and thermistor in sequence. Most ice maker problems close same-visit."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does Thermador refrigerator repair cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Diagnostic is $89, waived with repair. Typical repairs: evaporator fan motor $320–$460, condenser fan motor $285–$385, compressor start relay $85–$145, overload protector $65–$125, main control board $580–$920, inverter board (variable-speed compressor) $680–$1,050, door gasket $285–$420, ice maker module $285–$420, water inlet valve $165–$240, defrost thermostat $125–$195. Sealed-system compressor replacement runs $950–$1,650 with labor due to the brazing and vacuum work required."
        }
